This paper deals with decision making under uncertainty, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of axiomatic approaches and possibility theory suggests that this paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and decision making (cs.DM). The paper may also be relevant to mathematical aspects of decision making (cs.MA) and game theory (cs.GT) due to the use of axiomatic systems.
